The award-winning Crowne Plaza at the United Nations is located on New York's East Side, one block away from the United Nations and within walking distance of New York's legendary sites such as the Empire State Building, Times Square and Grand Central Terminal, as well as fantastic New York shopping and dining. Originally built as the Tudor Hotel in 1931, the building is now a recognized historical New York landmark. Because of its proximity to the United Nations, the hotel has long been home to many visiting diplomats and heads of state.<br />
<br />
The Crowne Plaza at the United Nations' 300 beautifully appointed guest rooms and suites are newly redecorated and feature modern amenities. The hotel offers non-smoking rooms and hotel rooms with facilities for disabled people.<br />
<br />
Fine dining options at the Crowne Plaza at the United Nations include Cecil's Bistro which serves traditional American fare. The hotel's Regency Lounge and Cecil's Bar offer light snacks and a variety of drinks. Room Service is available for hotel guests wishing to dine in the privacy of their room.<br />
<br />
Crowne Plaza at the United Nations offers flexible meeting and banquet facilities can cater for up to 120 guests in a reception setting. State-of-the-art audio-visual equipment is available together with the services of the hotel's  Business Center.<br />
<br />
For fitness and relaxation at the Crowne Plaza at the United Nations, a complimentary Fitness Center is available. The hotel's highly individual and gracious attention to a guest's needs is what makes the Crowne Plaza at the United Nations truly unique.<br />
<br />
Like all of the more than 100 Crowne Plaza hotels in the Americas, Crowne Plaza at the United Nations offers upscale amenities in a comfortable and elegant environment which helps you get your work done or relax while away from home.  Our brand is proud to offer 7:00 am check-in service, fitness centers, business centers and full-service restaurants at this and other locations around the Americas to keep you fit and productive while traveling.<br />
<br />
The Crowne Plaza at the United Nations is owned and operated by InterContinental<SUP><FONT SIZE="-1">TM</FONT></SUP> Hotels Group.
</p>
